## WHAT TO AVOID

### ❌ Never Do These:
- Use old color variables (accent, accent-light, accent-dark)
- Use old fonts (font-playfair, font-source, font-jakarta)
- Add emojis anywhere in content
- Create listicle-style headers ("1.", "2.", etc as main sections)
- Use excessive bolding or formatting
- Add localStorage or sessionStorage
- Use bright colors or gradients
- Create "card" style designs with rounded corners and shadows (except images)
- Use colored backgrounds (stick to bg-background or bg-foreground/5)
- Add decorative elements or icons
- Use multiple exclamation points!!!
- Write in second person excessively ("you should...")

### ✅ Always Do These:
- Start with category label → H1 → deck → hero image
- Use section dividers (border-t border-foreground/10)
- Include proper spacing between all elements
- Write in editorial third person when analyzing trends
- Use sophisticated vocabulary
- Include research, data, expert references
- Cite sources naturally in text
- Add proper image captions when context helps
- End with related topics section
- Include both article and FAQ schema
- Optimize for "how to" and question-based searches

